  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for python-pip",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for python-pip fixes the following issues\n\n- CVE-2026-3219: pip doesn't reject concatenated ZIP (bsc#1262429).\n- CVE-2026-6357: pip self-update functionality can import newly installed modules after wheel installation\n  (bsc#1263442).\n- CVE-2026-8643: path traversal via malicious entry point name in pip wheel installation allows arbitrary file overwrite\n  (bsc#1266669).\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
